  options , , Q  The answer must be a place where people usually obtain new soap. A supermarket is a common place to buy soap, and a good place to obtain new soap. Washing is a place where you wash your hands or something, not where you obtain soap. A cabinet is a place where soap is usually stored, not where you obtain it. Own home is a place where you can obtain new soap, but not the only place. So the answer is a supermarket (a).

